The paper proposes a deep neural network framework for detecting oriented scene text, which involves combining semantic segmentation and SSD. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a deep neural network, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves benchmarking and comparing the proposed method to other methods, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper involves text detection, which suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
